  "time_ut": 1659255910,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf  \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0dbd\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A big hole in the archeology gazette",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Officials of the Department of Archeology point out that since the four main buildings in Colombo, including the President's House, which were taken over by the militants, have not been formally and precisely declared by gazette notices, the enforcement of the law under the Antiquities Act has become problematic regarding the persons who damaged their ancient properties.",
        "They also mention that even though preliminary work has been done in relation to issuing a gazette notice, a perfect gazette notice stating that the Presidential Palace has been designated as an ancient place has not been issued yet.",
        "In this regard, in our inquiry to the Assistant Director of Archeology (Western Provinces) Shyamali Rajapaksa, she said that there is no specific gazette announcement mentioning the Presidential Palace as an ancient place.",
        "Due to this, the President's House Temple House, the President's Secretariat and the Prime Minister's Office are in the process of publishing gazette notices as ancient places, she said.",
        "Also, in the report, the Department of Archeology does not have a document about the antiques in the Presidential Palace.",
        "All these four buildings were taken over by a group of activists who protested in Colombo recently demanding the then President Gotabaya Rajapaksa to resign from his position.",
        "The police said that while the buildings were under the control of the militants, many ancient items were damaged and some other items were missing.",
        "Mrs. Shyamali Rajapaksa further said that a team of archeological officers is working to document the destroyed items.",
        "The activities are carried out under the special supervision of the Director General of Archaeology, Professor Anura Manatunga"
      ],
